<h3 class="mt4">1975</h3> 
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Randy is hired by Caymus as the Enologist</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1978</h3> 
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Randy and Lori purchase the “Trailer Vineyard” and begin farming 5 ½ acres of Cabernet in their free time and on the weekends. Jenny is born and the family moves into the white house.</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1979</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Randy harvests 9 tons of Cabernet Sauvignon from his vineyard and an adjoining vineyard that he manages. He also purchases 3 tons from the Beatty vineyard and produces 660 cases of 750ml’s, 28 cases of magnums and 53 five liter bottles, Dunn Vineyards begins…</p>

<p class="lh-copy measure center i">"The mountain really determined the style of the wine. It became obvious right away that the grapes up here were much more powerful than down on the valley floor. I just made the wine itself the same way we did at Caymus, it just was a more tannic wine due to the place."</p>
<p class="lh-copy measure center i">"I knew that I wanted to simplify things after my experience at Caymus. I didn’t want to be bottling into the back of a super market truck and didn’t want to be subjugated to the marketing department’s demands. “Keep it simple dummy.""</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1981</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">The winery is bonded, here in Angwin.</p>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Randy and Lori’s second daughter Kristina is born.</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1982</h3>

<p class="lh-copy measure center">(pic of 5L box) made by hand from a fallen Ponderosa Pine. Randy assists the Lamborn Family with their first wine, consults on Bill Smith’s La Jota project with Helen Turley.</p>

<p class="bg-light-silver lh-copy measure center">The 5L boxes were hand made here at the winery from a fallen Ponderosa Pine. Randy makes the first Lamborn Family wine. Randy consults on Bill Smith’s revived La Jota wine with Helen Turley.</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1983</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Randy makes the first Grace Family wine at the Caymus winery.</p> 
<p class="bg-light-silver lh-copy measure center">Randy makes the first Grace Family Cabernet. He had been making wine with this fruit at Caymus as a single vineyard wine.</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1984</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">ATF approves Howell Mountain AVA in January. The ’81 vintage is bottled and the 5L’s received etched bottles for the first time. Randy made the Livingstone – Moffett wine.</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1985</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Randy parts way with Caymus. Construction begins on the brown house. </p>

<h3 class="mt4">1986</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">The family moves into the brown house. Randy makes the first Pahlmeyer wine after offering to buy Jayson’s fruit. </p>

<h3 class="mt4">1987</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Raul Martinez is brought on the assist Randy in the vineyard, he was employee #1 and is still our vineyard manager to this day.</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1988</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Mike graduates from UC Santa Barbara</p>  

<h3 class="mt4">1989</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">The caves are dug. Dunn has more space to store its barrels and Jenny and Kristina get a roller rink!</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1991</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Mike marries Kara Pecota. Randy purchases the Park Muscatine Vineyard.</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1994</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Mike and Kara bring their first son and the first grandchild into the family as Alex is born.</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1995</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Erin Begerow joins the team and takes over the office management and mailing list coordination.</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1996</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Jennifer graduates HS</p>

<h3 class="mt4">1997</h3>
<p class="lh-copy measure center">Mike and Kara have a baby girl, the first granddaughter. Tatyana is born</p>

